(A) Evidence of Erosion: Immediately below Pascoe road bridge. Bank needs re-enforcement.
(D) Spawning distribution: Chum spawn estuary to Three Falls. Majority of coho spawn above Young Lake. Chinook often found at the confluence of Rocky Creek.
(E) Comments on predators: Blue Heron, Merganzers, Otters, and seals.
(F) Egg digging: At lower end below Pascoe Road.
(H) recommended enhancement: Presently enhanced by Jack Brooks Hatchery, net pen rearing in Young Lake and smolt trap.
(K) Additional comments: Of 30,000 coho reared in Young Lake Pen, only 11,000 migrated through smolt trap (as well as only 5000 wild spawn smolts). The issing 19, 000 Young Lake smolts are unaccounted for.
